{
  "stem": "4830.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And fortunately unsuccessfully, because they hit the bridge many, many times, but did not hit the pillars.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So our unit need eventuality was ordered to fix the bridge full time whenever each and every air raid.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had a specially designated unit there, which was completely killed by a previous air raid.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they escaped in a large crater that was made by a previous large bomb, with the idea that once a bomb fell in a place, another one would not fall there.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this wasn't true.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Another one fell there and this unit was completely wiped out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we took up fixing the bridge.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we suffered further losses.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now from there-- from Szob-- I took arbitrary leave several times.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They called this with a Jewish or Yiddish word, [YIDDISH], which meant that I had to be back within 24 hours.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If I am away for longer than 24 hours, this meant desertion, for which the punishment was death.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If I am back within 48 hours, they called it arbitrary leave for which the punishment was one week solitary.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we didn't worry about that that much.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I managed to escape from this place many times to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And in the meantime, my brother, who was with another unit, was transferred to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was in Budapest, but he was so law abiding that he refused to escape.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my father wanted to see him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He really loved him, and in order to satisfy this request, I-- from time to time when I escaped from Szob, I managed to travel to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I sneaked into his unit, I helped him out, and I stayed there until he came back, so the number count would fit.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because they counted numbers from time to time.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
